result.description:
Data Management Plan (DMP) – to include details of the management of the digital research data generated in the action, in particular regarding: 
(a) the research data repository and measures taken to make it possible for third parties to access, mine, exploit, reproduce and disseminate — free of charge for any user — the following:
(i) the data, including associated metadata, needed to validate the results presented in scientific publications;
(ii) other data, including associated metadata;
(b) information to be made available via the chosen repository about the tools and instruments at the disposal of the beneficiaries and necessary for validating the results e.g. specialised software or software code, algorithms and analysis protocols (and — where possible — provide the tools and instruments themselves).
